/-- The **Banach-Alaoglu theorem**: the polar set of a neighborhood `s` of the origin in a
normed space `E` is a compact subset of `weak_dual 𝕜 E`. -/
theorem is_compact_polar [ProperSpace 𝕜] {s : Set E} (s_nhd : s ∈ (nhds) (0 : E)) : IsCompact (polar 𝕜 s) :=
  is_compact_of_bounded_of_closed (bounded_polar_of_mem_nhds_zero 𝕜 s_nhd) (is_closed_polar _ _)
#align is_compact_polar is_compact_polar

theorem is_compact_of_bounded_of_closed [ProperSpace 𝕜] {s : Set (WeakDual 𝕜 E)}
    (hb : Bounded («expr ⁻¹' » dual.to_weak_dual s)) (hc : IsClosed s) : IsCompact s :=
  (Embedding.isCompact_iff_isCompact_image FunLike.coe_injective.embedding_induced).mpr <|

/-- The **Banach-Alaoglu theorem**: closed balls of the dual of a normed space `E` are compact in

theorem is_compact_closed_ball [ProperSpace 𝕜] (x' : dual 𝕜 E) (r : exprℝ) :

is_closed_polar:
/-- The polar `polar 𝕜 s` of a set `s : E` is a closed subset when the weak star topology
is used. -/
theorem is_closed_polar (s : Set E) : IsClosed (polar 𝕜 s) :=
  by
  simp only [polar_def, set_of_forall]
  exact isClosed_binterᵢ fun x hx => is_closed_Iic.preimage (WeakBilin.eval_continuous _ _).norm
#align is_closed_polar is_closed_polar

dual_norm_topology_le_weak_dual_topology:
/-- The weak-star topology is coarser than the dual-norm topology. -/
theorem dual_norm_topology_le_weak_dual_topology :
    (by infer_instance : TopologicalSpace (dual 𝕜 E)) ≤ (by infer_instance : TopologicalSpace (WeakDual 𝕜 E)) :=
  by
  convert to_weak_dual_continuous.le_induced
  exact induced_id.symm
#align dual_norm_topology_le_weak_dual_topology dual_norm_topology_le_weak_dual_topology
